            . I live about a quarter of a mile from Mr. Mott's. The morning that he was robbed, just after the clock had struck twelve, my dogs alarmed me. I threw up my sash, and saw three men, and a fourth was standing in the breach they had made in the pallisadoes; I can't swear to their faces; they ran away.</p>
